{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place carrots, leeks and turnips in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>7 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add potatoes, water, 1 tsp salt and 1 pinch ground black pepper. Line Varoma dish with baking paper and set in position. Add baby spinach to Varoma dish and season with 20 g butter and ½ tsp salt. Close Varoma and steam <nobr>20 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Remove Varoma, drain cooked spinach and divide between 8 heatproof ramekins (approx. Ø 7 cm, height 4 cm). Arrange diced tomatoes over the spinach. Crack 1 egg into each ramekin and season to taste with ½ tsp salt and 1 pinch ground black pepper. Arrange 3 ramekins in Varoma dish and 5 on Varoma tray, set Varoma back in position and cook for a further <nobr>11 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove Varoma and set aside.","Add remaining 20 g butter to mixing bowl, insert measuring cup and blend <strong><nobr>1 min\/speed 5<\/nobr>-10, increasing speed gradually<\/strong>. Serve soup hot as a starter, followed by eggs en cocotte with toasted bread fingers for dipping, along with salt and pepper for individual seasoning."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["400 g carrots, cut in pieces","300 g leeks, cut in pieces","200 g turnips, cut in pieces","100 g potatoes, cut in pieces (2 cm)","800 g water","2 tsp salt, plus extra to taste","2 pinches ground black pepper, plus extra to taste","200 g fresh baby spinach","40 g butter, cut in pieces","100 g tomatoes, diced","8 eggs, chilled (see tip)","400 g white bread, toasted, cut in fingers"]}],"id":"r150813","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/--WLgmIL4zNs\/XZaph1v4N9I\/AAAAAAAAhRw\/5aYOxARkKkMXcaqA9MCys0oV1ixQORY4QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_1KTefPP45hXan3JT.png","title":"Vegetable Soup, Eggs En Cocotte with Spinach","publishedAt":"2017-06-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"13 g","fat":"9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"34 g","calories":"1169 kJ \/ 279 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, ramekins (approx. Ø 7 cm, height 4 cm)","hintsAndTricks":["<i>The eggs, spinach and tomatoes are steamed in little dishes above a soup, perfect for lunch or a light dinner. Try sprinkling some cheese on top of the eggs before steaming, and feel free to adapt this warming winter soup to any season according to the vegetables you have at hand.<\/i>","For a different presentation, prepare and serve eggs in heatproof glass jars (max. height 4 cm) .<br>- The cooking time for the eggs in <nobr>step 3<\/nobr> can be adjusted according to their size, their temperature and your cooking preference. Chilled medium eggs <nobr>(53-63 g)<\/nobr> cooked as directed by the recipe will result in firm egg whites and runny egg yolks. If using room temperature eggs, cook <nobr><strong>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1.<\/strong><\/nobr> Increase cooking time by <nobr>1 min<\/nobr> <nobr>30 sec<\/nobr> if you prefer semi-hard egg yolks."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h","8 portions"]}